# hexa-lang /.roadmap — created 2026-04-26
# Re-introduced after 2026-04-25 retire (commit 3caebc54). Scope is
# narrow on purpose: hexa-lang-internal compiler/runtime work that
# does not belong in hive's SSOT. Cross-repo coordination still flows
# through hive/.roadmap.

# scope
#   hexa-lang = self-hosted compiler + runtime + stdlib.
#   This file tracks compiler/runtime ROI work; agent/UX/swarm work
#   belongs in hive. Per-repo SSOT files were retired 2026-04-25 in
#   favor of hive-as-sole-source, but compiler-internal initiatives
#   (toolchain, codegen backends, perf wedges) accumulated locally
#   without a registry — this file restores that registry only for
#   hexa-lang-internal scope.

# baseline (2026-04-26, post perf-32 + 02af1622 + 132d1e17 + 5401409e)
#   tool/changelog_parse.hexa cold aot_build_slot profile (16KB flat):
#     module_loader flatten   215ms   7%
#     hexa_v2 transpile        26ms   1%   (was 2,192ms pre-02af1622)
#     clang -O2 link        1,600ms  84%  ← dominant
#     other                  ~250ms   8%
#   hexa_full.hexa (753KB) transpile: 631ms.
#   codegen_c2.hexa (280KB) transpile: 147ms.
#   Conclusion: clang link is now the bottleneck on every cold compile
#   and every runtime.c edit invalidation.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# active entries
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- todo [SH1] self-host AOT — reduce/remove clang dependency
  goal:
    - per README "Self-hosted 100% .hexa" + ARM64/x86_64 target claims,
      current path is hexa → C → clang → native; aim is hexa →
      ARM64/x86_64 directly (or via cached object lib + faster cc).
  acceptance:
    - cold aot_build_slot ≥30% faster on tool/changelog_parse.hexa
    - byte-identical (or behaviourally identical) output vs baseline
    - all four bench targets (cold, warm, multi-use, trivial) measured
  stages:
    A) survey — self/native/, self/aarch64*/arm64*/codegen*/asm*/elf*/
       macho*/linker*/jit*, tool/build_native.hexa + other build scripts,
       README targets vs wired, bench/native, inter-repo (anima, nexus,
       n6-architecture, airgenome). Output: maturity table + blockers.
    B) wedge — pick smallest viable (highest "shipped/LOC"):
       W1 faster cc (clang→tcc/zig cc) via HEXA_AOT_CC env toggle
       W2 cached runtime.o object lib (verify _layers/link/ doesn't
          already cover; coordinate with Agent 3's 132d1e17 cache)
       W3 direct ARM64 codegen for trivial scripts + system `as`,
          fall back to clang for non-trivial — first real self-host
       W4 revive whatever survey turns up, if mature enough
    C) witness — bench 4 targets vs commit 02af1622 baseline:
       (1) tool/changelog_parse.hexa cold (clean cache)
       (2) same warm
       (3) tool/blocker_autofire.hexa (multi-use)
       (4) trivial println("hi") — worst case for clang fixed overhead
       Both correctness (byte/behaviour identical) and speed (≥30%).
  don't-touch (parallel-agent settled territory):
    - self/runtime.c              (perf-32 settled)
    - self/main.hexa              (Agent 3 layered cache; coordinate
                                   if a wedge enters aot_build_slot)
    - build/hexa_interp shim      (Agent 2 settled)
    - self/native/hexa_cc.c L1    (Agent 4 setenv)
    - hive/, anima/, nexus/       (read-only)
  do-touch:
    - new self/native/ codegen modules
    - tool/build_*.hexa (where wedge demands)
    - new tool/aot_cc_select.hexa (backend selector, if W1)
    - README.md targets section (only if a real backend ships)
  build-cycle:
    - hexa build self/main.hexa <out> → build/artifacts/app
    - replacing live /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/hexa REQUIRES
      `codesign --sign - --force /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/hexa`
      else macOS Gatekeeper SIGKILLs second invocation.
  exit-on-witness:
    - omega cycle: if wedge moves cold-compile <30%, that IS the
      witness — don't ship a "self-hosting" win that's slower than
      baseline. Document the blocker and surface next wedge.
  on-completion:
    - commit prefix: `feat(self-host):` or `perf(aot-cc):`
    - body must include: Stage A survey table + chosen wedge +
      rationale + Stage C measurements
    - update memory: project_hexa_perf32_aot_use_resolution.md OR
      new project_hexa_self_hosting_progress.md (if scope large)
    - document remaining clang surface + follow-up wedges
  related-memory:
    - /Users/ghost/.claude/projects/-Users-ghost-core-hive/memory/
      project_hexa_perf32_aot_use_resolution.md
    - /Users/ghost/.claude/projects/-Users-ghost-core-hive/memory/
      project_omega_saturation_cycle.md

